article.headline: Tulsa 92, Texas-San Antonio 67
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Justin Hurtt scored 33 points, his third consecutive game with at least 30, to lead Tulsa to a 92-67 victory against Texas-San Antonio on Thursday night. Stephen Idlet had 20 points for the Golden Hurricane (6-6). Melvin Johnson III led UTSA (6-4) with 17 points, and Devin Gibson added 13. Tulsa hit eight 3-pointers and shot 58 percent from the floor in the first half. Scottie Haralson made 5 of 7 shots from beyond the arc in the first half, added another 3-pointer after intermission and finished with 18 points. Hurtt made 11 of 17 shots, including six 3-pointers, in becoming the first Hurricane player to score 30 points in three straight games since Willie Biles in 1973-74.
